Spain&#8217;s state prosecutor would accept substituting a fine of 255,000 euros ($285,116) for the 21-month prison sentence handed down by a Barcelona court to soccer player Lionel Messi for tax fraud, Barcelona newspaper La Vanguardia reported on Friday.Messi and his father Jorge were found guilty by a Catalan court last July on three counts of tax fraud between 2007 and 2009 to the tune of 4.1 million euros on image rights and were also fined 2 million euros.Spain&#8217;s Supreme Court rejected in May an appeal by the Barcelona football star and stood by a Catalan regional court&#8217;s 21-month prison sentence.The state prosecutor was not immediately available to comment on Friday.-Reuters